HEADWORD: Actualist
<hw>Ac"tu*al*ist</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who deals with or
considers actually existing facts and conditions, rather than fancies or
theories; a realist; -- opposed to <ant>idealist</ant>.</def> <rj><au>J.
Grote.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

